::DrillBit::

"Sure, hon." He took off for the bridge. His audio recepters were going
to short cirquit if he had to listen to this much longer. He reached the
bridge, sitting in the comunication seat. He saw that something had
taked over the whole system, and that he was locked out. He opened a
comm.
"Kit, something is in the system. I'm locked out of computer access.
There is no way for be to turn it off."

:::Demolition:::

He was geting tired, the fight was a long one.

::Hot Rod::

He was in a trance, next to Feline's remains.
